{
  "info": {
    "name": "Penneo API",
    "description": "A collection for validating the Penneo API before integrating. Covers authentication, sending a casefile for signing, polling job status, checking casefile status, and retrieving documents.\n\n**Setup**\nAdd the following variables to this collection before running:\n- `clientId` — your OAuth client ID\n- `clientSecret` — your OAuth client secret\n- `apiKey` — your Penneo API key\n- `apiSecret` — your Penneo API secret\n\nThe `baseUrl` and `authUrl` are pre-configured for sandbox. Change them to the production URLs when you are ready to go live.\n\n**Flow**\nRun the requests in order — each one automatically saves the values needed by the next. Every request includes assertions that validate the response, so you can use the Collection Runner to verify the full flow end-to-end.\n\n**Token expiry**\nThe access token is valid for 10 minutes. If later requests fail with 401, re-run request 1 to get a fresh token.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "https://sandbox.penneo.com",
      "description": "Base URL for the Penneo API. Change to https://app.penneo.com for production."
    },
    {
      "key": "authUrl",
      "value": "https://sandbox.oauth.penneo.cloud",
      "description": "Base URL for the Penneo OAuth server. Change to https://login.penneo.com for production."
    },
    {
      "key": "clientId",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Your OAuth client ID."
    },
    {
      "key": "clientSecret",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Your OAuth client secret."
    },
    {
      "key": "apiKey",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Your Penneo API key."
    },
    {
      "key": "apiSecret",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Your Penneo API secret."
    },
    {
      "key": "accessToken",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Auto-set by request 1."
    },
    {
      "key": "base64Nonce",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Auto-set by request 1 pre-request script. Used internally for WSSE auth."
    },
    {
      "key": "createdAt",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Auto-set by request 1 pre-request script. Used internally for WSSE auth."
    },
    {
      "key": "digest",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Auto-set by request 1 pre-request script. Used internally for WSSE auth."
    },
    {
      "key": "jobUuid",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Auto-set by request 2."
    },
    {
      "key": "payloadHash",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Auto-set by request 2."
    },
    {
      "key": "casefileId",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Auto-set by request 3 once the job completes. Can also be set manually."
    },
    {
      "key": "documentId",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Auto-set by request 4 to the first document ID. Update manually to download a specific document."
    },
    {
      "key": "documentIds",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Auto-set by request 4 as a JSON array of all document IDs in the casefile."
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Get Access Token",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const apiSecret = pm.collectionVariables.get('apiSecret');",
              "const apiKey = pm.collectionVariables.get('apiKey');",
              "const clientId = pm.collectionVariables.get('clientId');",
              "const clientSecret = pm.collectionVariables.get('clientSecret');",
              "",
              "const missing = [];",
              "if (!clientId) missing.push('clientId');",
              "if (!clientSecret) missing.push('clientSecret');",
              "if (!apiKey) missing.push('apiKey');",
              "if (!apiSecret) missing.push('apiSecret');",
              "if (missing.length > 0) {",
              "    throw new Error('Missing required collection variables: ' + missing.join(', ') + '. Set them in the collection Variables tab.');",
              "}",
              "",
              "const nonceWordArray = CryptoJS.lib.WordArray.random(20);",
              "const base64Nonce = nonceWordArray.toString(CryptoJS.enc.Base64);",
              "const createdAt = new Date().toISOString();",
              "",
              "// digest = Base64(SHA1(nonce + createdAt + apiSecret))",
              "const digest = CryptoJS.SHA1(",
              "    nonceWordArray",
              "    .concat(CryptoJS.enc.Utf8.parse(createdAt))",
              "    .concat(CryptoJS.enc.Utf8.parse(apiSecret))",
              ").toString(CryptoJS.enc.Base64);",
              "",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('base64Nonce', base64Nonce);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('createdAt', createdAt);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('digest', digest);"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const json = pm.response.json();",
              "",
              "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response contains access_token', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('access_token').that.is.a('string').and.is.not.empty;",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('expires_in').that.is.a('number');",
              "});",
              "",
              "if (json.access_token) {",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', json.access_token);",
              "    console.log('Access token saved. Expires in ' + json.expires_in + ' seconds.');",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{authUrl}}/oauth/token",
          "host": ["{{authUrl}}"],
          "path": ["oauth", "token"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"client_id\": \"{{clientId}}\",\n  \"client_secret\": \"{{clientSecret}}\",\n  \"grant_type\": \"api_keys\",\n  \"key\": \"{{apiKey}}\",\n  \"nonce\": \"{{base64Nonce}}\",\n  \"created_at\": \"{{createdAt}}\",\n  \"digest\": \"{{digest}}\"\n}",
          "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
        },
        "description": "Authenticates using the API Keys Grant flow. The pre-request script automatically calculates the nonce, timestamp, and SHA1 digest — no manual setup needed beyond setting your collection variables.\n\nThe access token is valid for 10 minutes and is automatically saved to `accessToken` for use in subsequent requests."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Send Casefile",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const token = pm.collectionVariables.get('accessToken');",
              "if (!token) {",
              "    throw new Error('accessToken is not set. Run request 1 first.');",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const json = pm.response.json();",
              "",
              "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response contains at least one job', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('jobs').that.is.an('array').and.is.not.empty;",
              "    pm.expect(json.jobs[0]).to.have.property('uuid').that.is.a('string').and.is.not.empty;",
              "    pm.expect(json.jobs[0]).to.have.property('payloadHash').that.is.a('string').and.is.not.empty;",
              "});",
              "",
              "if (json.jobs && json.jobs.length > 0) {",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set('jobUuid', json.jobs[0].uuid);",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set('payloadHash', json.jobs[0].payloadHash);",
              "    console.log('Job UUID saved: ' + json.jobs[0].uuid);",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "X-Auth-Token", "value": "{{accessToken}}" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/send/api/v1/casefiles/20251022/create",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["send", "api", "v1", "casefiles", "20251022", "create"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "formdata",
          "formdata": [
            {
              "key": "data",
              "value": "{\n  \"caseFile\": {\n    \"title\": \"Contract Agreement\",\n    \"signers\": [\n      {\n        \"name\": \"John Doe\",\n        \"email\": \"john@example.com\",\n        \"role\": \"signer\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"documents\": [\n      {\n        \"title\": \"Contract Document\",\n        \"name\": \"contract.pdf\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}",
              "description": "JSON string describing the casefile. The document 'name' must exactly match the filename of the uploaded file.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "key": "files",
              "description": "Select your PDF file here. The filename must match the 'name' field in the data JSON above.",
              "type": "file",
              "src": []
            }
          ]
        },
        "description": "Creates a new casefile with one or more documents and signers.\n\nThe request uses `multipart/form-data` with two parts:\n- `data`: a JSON string describing the casefile (title, signers, documents)\n- `files`: the PDF file(s) to be signed\n\n**Important:** The `name` field in the documents array must exactly match the filename of the uploaded PDF.\n\nThe casefile is created asynchronously. Use the returned `uuid` and `payloadHash` (auto-saved) to poll for completion in request 3.\n\nAuthentication uses `X-Auth-Token` (not `Authorization: Bearer`) — this is specific to the send endpoint."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Poll Job Status",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const jobUuid = pm.collectionVariables.get('jobUuid');",
              "const payloadHash = pm.collectionVariables.get('payloadHash');",
              "",
              "if (!jobUuid || !payloadHash) {",
              "    throw new Error('jobUuid or payloadHash is not set. Run request 2 first.');",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const json = pm.response.json();",
              "",
              "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response contains jobStatus', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('jobStatus').that.is.a('string');",
              "    pm.expect(['pending', 'processing', 'completed', 'failed', 'aborted_duplicated']).to.include(json.jobStatus);",
              "});",
              "",
              "console.log('Job status: ' + json.jobStatus);",
              "",
              "if (json.jobStatus === 'completed' && json.result) {",
              "    pm.test('Completed job contains caseFile ID', function () {",
              "        pm.expect(json.result).to.have.nested.property('data.caseFile.id');",
              "    });",
              "    const casefileId = json.result.data.caseFile.id;",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set('casefileId', casefileId);",
              "    console.log('Casefile ID saved: ' + casefileId);",
              "} else if (json.jobStatus === 'failed') {",
              "    pm.test('Job should not fail', function () {",
              "        pm.expect.fail('Job failed: ' + (json.errorMessage || 'no error message'));",
              "    });",
              "} else if (json.jobStatus === 'aborted_duplicated') {",
              "    pm.test('Job should not be a duplicate', function () {",
              "        pm.expect.fail('Job was aborted as a duplicate submission.');",
              "    });",
              "} else {",
              "    console.log('Job not yet complete (' + json.jobStatus + '). Re-run this request until it completes.');",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/send/api/v1/queue/public/status",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["send", "api", "v1", "queue", "public", "status"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"uuid\": \"{{jobUuid}}\",\n  \"payloadHash\": \"{{payloadHash}}\"\n}",
          "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
        },
        "description": "Polls the status of the casefile creation job submitted in request 2.\n\nPossible statuses:\n- `pending` — job is queued, not yet started\n- `processing` — job is being processed\n- `completed` — casefile created successfully\n- `failed` — something went wrong (see `errorMessage`)\n- `aborted_duplicated` — a duplicate submission was detected\n\nThis endpoint does not require authentication — the `uuid` and `payloadHash` together serve as verification.\n\nRate limited to 20 requests per minute. Re-run this request until the status is `completed`."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4. Check Casefile Status",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const token = pm.collectionVariables.get('accessToken');",
              "const casefileId = pm.collectionVariables.get('casefileId');",
              "",
              "if (!token) {",
              "    throw new Error('accessToken is not set. Run request 1 first (token may have expired after 10 minutes).');",
              "}",
              "if (!casefileId) {",
              "    throw new Error('casefileId is not set. Run request 3 until the job status is completed, or set it manually.');",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const json = pm.response.json();",
              "",
              "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response contains casefile data', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('id');",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('status');",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('documents').that.is.an('array');",
              "});",
              "if (json.documents && json.documents.length > 0) {",
              "    const ids = json.documents.map(d => d.id);",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set('documentIds', JSON.stringify(ids));",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set('documentId', ids[0]);",
              "    if (ids.length === 1) {",
              "        console.log('Document ID saved: ' + ids[0]);",
              "    } else {",
              "        console.log('Multiple documents found (' + ids.length + '). All IDs saved to documentIds: ' + JSON.stringify(ids));",
              "        console.log('documentId is set to the first: ' + ids[0] + '. Update it manually for other documents, or use the Collection Runner to iterate.');",
              "    }",
              "} else {",
              "    console.warn('No documents found in casefile response.');",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/casefiles/{{casefileId}}",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "casefiles", "{{casefileId}}"]
        },
        "description": "Retrieves the full details of a casefile by ID, including its status and the status of each signer.\n\nSigner statuses:\n- `0` Request sent\n- `1` Request opened\n- `2` Opened\n- `3` Signed\n- `4` Rejected\n\nCasefile statuses:\n- `0` Draft\n- `1` Pending\n- `2` Rejected\n- `3` Deleted\n- `5` Completed\n- `7` Expired\n\nThe first document ID is automatically saved to `documentId` for use in request 5."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "5. Get Document",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const token = pm.collectionVariables.get('accessToken');",
              "const documentId = pm.collectionVariables.get('documentId');",
              "",
              "if (!token) {",
              "    throw new Error('accessToken is not set. Run request 1 first (token may have expired after 10 minutes).');",
              "}",
              "if (!documentId) {",
              "    throw new Error('documentId is not set. Run request 4 first, or set it manually.');",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response is a PDF', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type')).to.include('application/pdf');",
              "});",
              "",
              "console.log('Document downloaded. Size: ' + pm.response.responseSize + ' bytes.');"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" },
          { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/pdf" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v3/documents/{{documentId}}/content",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v3", "documents", "{{documentId}}", "content"]
        },
        "description": "Downloads a document as a PDF using the `documentId` variable set in request 4.\n\nSet the response type to 'Send and Download' in Postman to save the file locally.\n\n**Multiple documents:** If the casefile has more than one document, all IDs are available in the `documentIds` variable (JSON array). To download each one, either update `documentId` manually and re-run, or use the Postman Collection Runner with the following pre-request script to iterate:\n\n```js\nconst ids = JSON.parse(pm.collectionVariables.get('documentIds'));\nconst index = pm.info.iteration;\npm.collectionVariables.set('documentId', ids[index]);\n```\n\nTo download a JSON representation instead of a PDF, change the `Accept` header to `application/json`."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "6. Delete Casefile",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const token = pm.collectionVariables.get('accessToken');",
              "const casefileId = pm.collectionVariables.get('casefileId');",
              "",
              "if (!token) {",
              "    throw new Error('accessToken is not set. Run request 1 first (token may have expired after 10 minutes).');",
              "}",
              "if (!casefileId) {",
              "    throw new Error('casefileId is not set. Run request 3 until the job status is completed, or set it manually.');",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "console.log('Casefile ' + pm.collectionVariables.get('casefileId') + ' deleted.');"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "DELETE",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/casefiles/{{casefileId}}",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "casefiles", "{{casefileId}}"]
        },
        "description": "Permanently deletes a casefile by ID.\n\n**Note:** Only casefiles in draft or pending state can be deleted. A casefile that has been completed or rejected cannot be deleted.\n\nThis action is irreversible."
      }
    }
  ]
}
